    "result": "`internal/watch` watches the filesystem with `fsnotify` and re-runs a full `index.Indexer.Run` pass after a quiet window of file-save events. It intentionally skips per-file incremental logic — the indexer's content-hash diffing handles that. It also supports two hooks: `AfterIndex` (runs after each successful flush, e.g. to refresh the Go static graph) and `OnIdle` (fires after a quiet period post-flush, used to drain background summarization).\n\n**Debounce default: `500 ms`** (`watch.go:71`).",
